docs\sessions\deploy-health-audit-20260530.md:10:- **The phenotype.space VitePress subdomains are systemically broken by a base-path mismatch.** Each site is built with `base: '/<RepoName>/'` (for the `kooshapari.github.io/<Repo>/` deploy) but the **same bundle** is served at the custom-domain **root** `/`. Every `/<Repo>/assets/*.js|.css` then 404s, so pages load an unstyled, non-interactive HTML shell. Confirmed on `dino.phenotype.space` (33 errors) and `hwledger.phenotype.space` (34 errors).
docs\sessions\deploy-health-audit-20260530.md:11:- **DINOForge's own VitePress Pages deploy was failing in CI for days** (3 distinct build errors), so `kooshapari.github.io/Dino` and `dino.phenotype.space` were serving a stale bundle. **All 3 build errors + the base-path asset bug are now fixed and committed** (`506a6bb8`); build exits 0 locally.
docs\sessions\deploy-health-audit-20260530.md:12:- **agileplus Pages = not deployed at all** ("Site not found"); every `deploy.yml` run is failing. Same VitePress build class — needs the same triage as Dino.
